title: 820-4924-A boots, but freezes right at login screen
message:
came in yesterday, customer spilt cocktail on it, wouldnt turn on at all.

After replacing SMC, U5110 and U1950, and a good clean w/ flux the board works again.
Computer boots up, but freezes on loginscreen, regardless of which SSD i put in (my own test-SSD as well)

Have read up a little on this forum, but its hard to measure anything when the board is in the case and it shuts down or freezes.

Have looked at the CPU Vcore mosfets, they did have some liquid damage so decided to replace all four of them (should i have replaced the U7310 and U7320 at the same time?
any other hints to what i could look for?

title: 820-4924-A boots, but freezes right at login screen
message: Could really be anything....Something around Vcore is very possible, but anything else is also possible. I know that is not what you wanted to hear....
